As a result of the Title IX, there was a tremendous increase in the budget of women's athletics at A&M.
During your years here, the budget increased from $104,000 to $420,000.
Was the increase in the budget evident to you during your years here?
The first year, I was the only one on scholarship, and of course then it was separate coaches.
So I thought that was really interesting.
And it was real hard for the men to accept some of the men that were on there were only getting books and tuition,
and they'd compare their stuff to this other girl over here who was on there.
So.
You could definitely tell, and the coach got a bigger increase.
So you could definitely tell when they came in.
From its inception, most colleges in the NCAA have been against Title IX.
They argued that an equal funding of men's and women's athletics would be an economic disaster for college athletics.
Do you feel this is a viable reason to disallow women an equal opportunity with men to enjoy athletics?
Well, I know that some of the schools, you know, they don't want it.
